(232, 95, 'description', 'Night Rydazz is a project that I and a few other students undertook in Spring 2011. The project helped us develop a combination of electrical engineering, industrial design, and computer science skills and concepts in order to create a working physical prototype. We created a module lined with LED\'s that attaches to a bike wheel and flashes patterns in order to display text, pictures, or designs as you ride the bike around at night. Together we designed, built, and fabricated the pieces to make the prototype functional. I created this web site in order to present the prototype and explain its functionality and the creation of the project.'),
