(114, 1, '2012-12-06 02:32:03', '2012-12-06 02:32:03', 'Problem statement:\n<div>\n\n<em>Using the elements of design covered in class, create a final version of your personal poster. Look for ways to modify and refine the composition and typography. Expand beyond the grayscale color palette of your first poster. Develop the formal elements of the poster, both the graphical elements within the page and the size and shape of the entire poster (minimum size of 16\" x 16\"). Sharpen the conceptual approach of your project.</em>\n\n</div>\nSince the poster was supposed to display our most important hopes and desires, I tried to communicate the idea that sometimes those who are the most important to us and the most dear to us are those that hurt us the most. This idea represents a very stark contrast of emotions and therefore I had to be careful as to balance those emotions equally.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<hr />\n\n&nbsp;\n\n', 'Personal Poster 2.0', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '83-autosave', '', '', '2012-12-06 02:32:03', '2012-12-06 02:32:03', '', 83, 'http://jrstrauss.net/portfolio-new/83-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
