(523, 1, '2013-01-31 04:03:40', '2013-01-31 04:03:40', 'Back in the day (you know, the age of grandpas and dinosaurs), people did all mathematical calculations using only pen and paper. Sure, maybe they had tools like simple calculators and protractors, but certainly nothing that even comes close to the power of technology in present-day. Computing has completely changed the face of mathematics. What used to take hours to calculate and was extremely prone to error on the many steps towards the solution can now be calculated in nanoseconds. But in order to get to this point (enter trusty programmer), someone had to procedurally define these functions and algorithms. Here are a few examples of functions and mathematical processes in the field of Calculus and Linear Algebra that I translated from paper to terminal. I calculated each function to the 20th degree and analyzed the margin of error.', 'Computational Calculus', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '71-autosave', '', '', '2013-01-31 04:03:40', '2013-01-31 04:03:40', '', 71, 'http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/71-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
