r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"section\">\r\n<h1>Awards</h1>\r\n<div class=\"subsection\">+ One of Computational Media\'s \"Most Outstanding Students\" in the degree\r\n+ Dean\'s List each semester Fall 2008 to Spring 2012\r\n+ Best school-wide Foreign Language Student in high school</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"section work-experience\">\r\n<h1>Work Experience</h1>\r\n<div class=\"subsection\">\r\n<div class=\"left\">May 2012 - present</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">SolDesign Company\r\n<em>Front &amp; Back-end Web Developer</em>\r\nSolDesign is a small 12-person Web Agency that specializes in both Web Design and Web Development. We design, build, host, and maintain sites for our clients, doing all work in-house. My roles as a developer at SolDesign vary: front-end & back-end development, server management, site architecture, client management, migration, content management, and debugging & updating outdated products.</div>\r\n<div class=\"clear\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"subsection\">\r\n<div class=\"left\">December 2011 - May 2012</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">Crawford Media Services\r\n<em>Front &amp; Back-end Web Developer</em>\r\nI was hired as a contractor for six months to build a new web site for Crawford that would improve upon their current design and showcase their skill in the video production industry. I worked on the front-end and back-end of the site, communicating with the design team and interpreting the functional requirements for Crawford while critiquing the quality of the design and user experience of the site\'s interface.</div>\r\n<div class=\"clear\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"subsection\">\r\n<div class=\"left\">May 2011 - August 2012</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">The Children\'s School\r\n<em>Robotics Teacher</em>\r\nThe Children\'s School is a private school in Atlanta next to Piedmont Park. I taught the sixth grade technology class Computer Science and Robotics weekly using Lego NXT Mindstorms and basic lessons in the fundamentals of computing and procedural programming.</div>\r\n<div class=\"clear\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"subsection\">\r\n<div class=\"left\">August 2009 - May 2012</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">Institute for Computing Education\r\n<em>Summer Camp Director, Workshop Leader, Inventory Manager</em>\r\nThe Institute for Computing Education is a research institute funded by the National Science Foundation dedicated to raising interest in Computer Science among kids elementary through high school, especially among women and minorities. I led eight weeks of summer camps each summer, taught workshops throughout the school year, and managed their inventory throughout the year.</div>\r\n<div class=\"clear\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"subsection\">\r\n<div class=\"left\">January 2009 - August 2010</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">Office of Success Programs\r\n<em>Undergraduate Tutor</em>\r\nTutoring other undergrads in Computer Science and Spanish.</div>\r\n<div class=\"clear\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"section references\">\r\n<h1>References</h1>\r\n<div class=\"subsection\">\r\n<div class=\"left\">Tamara Weinstein</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">The Children\'s School, Technology Specialist\r\ntamaraw@thechildrensschool.com\r\n404.835.4602</div>\r\n<div class=\"clear\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"subsection\">\r\n<div class=\"left\">Barb Ericson</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">Institute for Computing Education, Director\r\nbe15@mail.gatech.edu\r\n404.702.7993</div>\r\n<div class=\"clear\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"subsection\">\r\n<div class=\"left\">Michael Allenberg</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">Crawford Media Services\r\nUser Interface Designer\r\nmallenberg@crawford.com\r\n678.641.2914</div>\r\n<div class=\"clear\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Resume', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '77-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-03-20 18:43:11', '2013-03-20 18:43:11', '', 77, 'http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/77-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
